title: Example Domain
content: Example Domain. This domain is for use in illustrative examples in documents. You may use this domain in literature without prior coordination or asking for permission.

title: IANA — IANA-managed Reserved Domains
content: IANA manages a list of domains that are reserved for use in documentation and examples. These include example.com, example.net, and example.org.

title: MDN Web Docs — HTTP
content: Hypertext Transfer Protocol (HTTP) is an application-layer protocol for transmitting hypermedia documents, such as HTML. It was designed for communication between web browsers and web servers.
